  <front>
   <head>OBSERVATION.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">LET the vain avaricious with oaths safely bind,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Lest either forgetfully rove;</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">The band of affection secureth the mind,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">When the wishes are centered in love.</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">If virtue alone is the guide of the will,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">Distrust has no right to be there;</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">The swain has no reason to doubt of his skill,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+" line_length="9">And the fair one has'nothing to fear.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
